@startuml agent-orchestration
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam dpi 130
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 13
skinparam noteFontSize 11
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fffae6
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #444444
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #888888
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #f6f8ff
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #6677aa
skinparam sequenceReferenceBackgroundColor #f6f8ff

title AgentAid — Planner / Worker Agent Orchestration\n(tools · interactions · async + concurrency)

actor      "CLI / digests API\n__main__.py"                        as User
participant "Planner Agent\nPydantic AI · role=planner\nsonnet-4-6" as Planner
participant "Worker Agent\nPydantic AI · role=worker\nsonnet-4-6"   as Worker
participant "tools.py\n(plain async functions)"                     as Tools
participant "Anthropic API\nllm.text · llm.vision · llm.json_call"  as LLM
database    "arXiv client\nmock (default) | real (env flag)"        as Arxiv
queue       "Run-scoped side-channels\n_RUN_FIGURES · figures_ctx"  as Side

User -> Planner ++ : await agent.run(user_prompt, deps=PlannerInput)
note right of Planner
  Single OTel root span for the whole run.
  Every @agent.tool call below becomes a
  child span via the GenAI integration in
  agentaid.otel.
end note

== Stage 1 — Candidate selection (sequential awaits) ==

loop planner LLM tool-use loop (planner.md system prompt)
  Planner -> LLM : messages.create(\n  tools=[search_arxiv, fetch_metadata,\n         score_candidate, dispatch_worker,\n         compose_digest])
  LLM --> Planner : tool_calls

  alt search_arxiv
    Planner -> Tools : await search_arxiv(q, limit, date_from, date_to)
    Tools -> Arxiv : client.search(...)
    Arxiv --> Tools : list[PaperSummary]
    Tools --> Planner : rows
  else fetch_metadata
    Planner -> Tools : await fetch_metadata(paper_id)
    Tools -> Arxiv : client.fetch_metadata(...)
    Arxiv --> Tools : PaperSummary
    Tools --> Planner : meta
  else score_candidate
    Planner -> Tools : await score_candidate(meta_id, interest)
    Tools -> LLM : llm.json_call(scoring prompt)
    LLM --> Tools : {score, rationale}
    Tools --> Planner : CandidateScore
  end
end

== Stage 2 — Per-paper deep read (fan-out: the concurrency point) ==

note over Planner, Worker
  The planner LLM emits **N dispatch_worker tool calls** in one
  assistant turn (Anthropic parallel tool use). Pydantic AI awaits
  them with **asyncio.gather** — N worker agents run in parallel,
  each with its own nested LLM-tool loop and its own OTel span tree.
end note

par
  Planner -> Worker ++ : dispatch_worker(p1)\nawait worker.run(prompt, WorkerInput(p1))
  Worker -> Tools : await fetch_paper(p1)
  Tools -> Arxiv : client.fetch_paper(p1)
  Arxiv --> Tools : Paper.body
  Tools --> Worker : body
  Worker -> Tools : await extract_figures(p1)
  loop per figure (sequential await)
    Tools -> LLM : llm.vision(image_bytes,\n"Describe what this figure shows")
    LLM --> Tools : description
  end
  Tools -> Side : _RUN_FIGURES[p1] = [...]
  Tools --> Worker : list[FigureDescription]
  Worker -> Tools : await summarize(p1, focus)
  Tools -> LLM : llm.text(sonnet, max=600)
  LLM --> Tools : bullets
  Tools --> Worker : Summary
  Worker --> Planner -- : WorkerResult
  Planner -> Side : figures_ctx[p1] = [...]\n(captured inside dispatch_worker tool)
else
  Planner -> Worker ++ : dispatch_worker(p2)\nawait worker.run(prompt, WorkerInput(p2))
  note over Worker : same tool sequence as p1\n(fetch_paper → extract_figures →\n summarize)
  Worker --> Planner -- : WorkerResult
else
  Planner -> Worker ++ : dispatch_worker(pN)\nawait worker.run(prompt, WorkerInput(pN))
  note over Worker : same tool sequence as p1\n(fetch_paper → extract_figures →\n summarize)
  Worker --> Planner -- : WorkerResult
end

== Stage 3 — Digest synthesis (single await) ==

Planner -> Tools : await compose_digest(sections, interest)
Tools -> LLM : llm.text(sonnet, max=2000)
LLM --> Tools : Markdown digest
Tools --> Planner : digest

Planner --> User -- : PlannerResult\n{digest, candidates, sections, figures}

== Stage 4 — Post-run merge & OTel emit ==

note over User, Side
  __main__.py merges figures from three sources in **increasing-trust** order:
  PlannerResult.figures  →  figures_ctx  →  _RUN_FIGURES (deterministic, wins).
  Then computes citation-weight attribution from section lengths and emits
  everything as OTel attributes on the root span:
  **agentaid.input · agentaid.output · agentaid.attribution · gen_ai.\***
  …which the agentaid SDK exports to the server's /ingest endpoint.
end note

@enduml
